{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Prohibit District Councils from applying to themselves for planning permission",
        "additional_details": "Planning Authority decisions must be completely independent of the applicant. District Councils running Trading Arms (wholly-or-partially-owned) who apply for planning permission present the planning team with a serious conflict of interest and their ability to remain truly independent must be questioned. \r\n\r\nDistrict Councils should not be allowed to own or have interests in development oriented businesses.",
        "background": "Prohibit District Councils from applying for planning permission from themselves via shell / trading arm companies masquerading as independent businesses but which are wholly-or-partly-owned companies of the District Council who are also in charge of the Local Planning Authority.",
